requirement:
Century Wind Power project management team is responsible for several             different phases of the project preparation and execution. Our major scope is     fabrication of offshore wind foundations (jackets, monopiles, transition pieces,  etc.) in all kinds of offshore wind projects with different requirements. Together with the project management team spanning the project life, you will be               responsible for initiating, planning, execution, and handing over the fabrication and supply project of offshore foundations. During the project execution             process, we also focus on building up the qualified supply chains locally and        internationally and establishing a sustainable management system for the           raising business. We are currently looking for several competent project               engineers or managers to execute the mega project and assist the team to          achieve the target as well as to fulfil the requirement of our clients.

Job Description:
1.	Assists and supports the project manager for execution, control and reports;
2.	Duly accomplishes the tasks and activities which are appointed;
3.	Regularly reports or feedback the progress and actively figures out the           solutions;
4.	Maintains the project document to ensure all in the right track;
5.	Keeps learning and cultivating the knowledges in project management and offshore technologies;
6.	Works in an intensive English spoken environment plus huge demands of      local communication.

